          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "1USABRK"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The experiment was performed at the",
                "Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory's 88-in.",
                "cyclotron"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Stack of alternating layers of thin gold and aluminum",
                "foils. The aluminum foils served as degraders,",
                "decreasing the 13C energy between each gold foil.",
                "  Foil         Thickness   Mean energy   Energy loss",
                "  No.   Mat.   (mg/cm2)         (MeV)       (MeV)",
                "  1     Au     1.93+-0.10   129.3+-0.7      1.36",
                "  2     Al     6.8+-1.0     124.4+-0.9      8.39",
                "  3     Au     1.93+-0.10   119.5+-1.5      1.44",
                "  4     Al     6.8+-1.0     114.3+-1.7      8.93",
                "  5     Au     2.32+-0.11   109.0+-2.1      1.83",
                "  6     Al     6.8+-1.0     103.6+-2.3      9.63",
                "  7     Au     1.93+-0.10    97.6+-2.7      1.63",
                "  8     Al     6.8+-1.0      91.5+-2.9      10.5",
                "  9     Au     1.93+-0.10    85.4+-3.4      1.77",
                " 10     Al     6.8+-1.0      78.7+-3.6      11.7",
                " 11     Au     1.9+-0.5      71.8+-4.3      1.96",
                " 12     Al     6.8+-1.0      64.2+-4.5      13.4",
                " 13     Au     1.9+-0.5      56.3+-5.5      2.22",
                " 14     Al     6.8+-1.0      47.1+-5.8     16.3",
                " 15     Al     6.8+-1.0      28.1+-7.6     21.6",
                " 16     Al     6.8+-1.0       8.7+-11.0    17.3",
                " 17     Au     1.9+-0.5 0     0.00"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Samples were counted sequentially on a single",
                "HPGe detector in a consistent geometry to minimize",
                "systematic uncertainties."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Following irradiation the samples were",
                "transported to the underground,low-background nuclear",
                "counting facility (NCF) at Lawrence Livermore",
                "National Laboratory."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CHSEP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The gold was chemically separated because of",
                "high background contributions from fusion-evaporation",
                "residue. The chemical separation improved the",
                "signal-to-background ratio, by orders of magnitude",
                "in. The absolute efficiencies of separation,",
                "typically on the order of 90%, were determined",
                "individually for the foils by comparing the 196gAu",
                "activity measured before and after separation."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Analysis of multiple decay chains and interfering",
                "gamma rays was performed using linear algebra to",
                "decouple direct production of a daughter nucleus",
                "from ingrowth due to a parent nucleus. At each",
                "incident energy a system of matrix equations is set",
                "up and diagonalized that contain the decay equations,",
                "cross sections, and reaction channels."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The cross-section uncertainties were",
                "determined from the Hessian matrix, composed of the",
                "second derivatives of the chi-squared function with",
                "respect to all pairs of parameters. The error matrix",
                "is then given by the inverse of the Hessian matrix."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "HISTORY": [
